narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about paleoclimate proxies and how archaeologist use/understand them.
I learned about the paleo climate and many of the basics of it

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course is great. I was never stressed or overwhelmed and feel like I learned something every week. I can't see really any weaknesses with it.
This is a great course that was extremely helpful in increasing my paleo climate knowledge

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, the workload of the course was such that it did not overwhelm my schedule, and I really did look forward to coming to class every week. Moreover, since there were not any exams for the course, I was able to focus on the material from the course that really interested me, and found myself researching those topics on my own outside of class and the assigned readings.
Yep! Chill workload, hilarious and very cool professors and TAs, and the final project is a lot of fun.
Absolutely. Professor McIntosh is awesome. Very fun class.
Yes. Great class and great professor
